10/07/2003
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal decided Wednesday (9 July) to release Bosnian Croat Zdravko Mucic, who has served two-thirds of his sentence. 
He had been sentenced to nine years in prison for crimes committed by subordinates while he commanded the camp at Celebici, in central Bosnia and Herzegovina. 
The crimes included the murders of nine prisoners. 
(SRNA, HINA, BBC - 09/07/03)
